97
00:05:41,404 --> 00:05:42,924
- Great.
- Hey Robby?

98
00:05:42,954 --> 00:05:44,154
New boss coming in
to make some cuts?

99
00:05:44,524 --> 00:05:46,204
I have no idea.

100
00:05:46,824 --> 00:05:48,384
Aren't you sitting down with him?

101
00:05:48,393 --> 00:05:49,393
Yes I am.

102
00:05:49,394 --> 00:05:50,524
So is it about Spotlight?

103
00:05:50,853 --> 00:05:51,853
I don't know Mike.

104
00:05:51,854 --> 00:05:52,894
But I do know...

105
00:05:52,954 --> 00:05:55,894
That Ben needs an answer on
that crime number story.

106
00:05:56,534 --> 00:05:59,094
I'm telling you, I really don't
think that story is for us.

107
00:06:04,704 --> 00:06:05,704
Mr Baron.

108
00:06:06,744 --> 00:06:07,944
Walter Robinson.

109
00:06:07,994 --> 00:06:08,994
Robby.

110
00:06:09,434 --> 00:06:10,954
Thanks for taking
a time of your...

111
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:12,404
- Oh, it's my pleasure.
- Appreciate it.

112
00:06:17,674 --> 00:06:18,724
Oh, yeah.

113
00:06:19,054 --> 00:06:20,244
Great book.

114
00:06:20,384 --> 00:06:22,534
Globe has a season
tickets at Fenway...

115
00:06:22,584 --> 00:06:23,984
once you settle in, by the way.

116
00:06:24,324 --> 00:06:25,564
Thank you.

117
00:06:25,724 --> 00:06:28,564
To be honest, I'm not
much of baseball fan...

118
00:06:28,594 --> 00:06:31,054
I'm just trying to get
the feel for the city.

119
00:06:31,664 --> 00:06:33,174
Oh, yeah.

120
00:06:33,634 --> 00:06:35,134
So, you're originally from Boston?

121
00:06:35,344 --> 00:06:37,124
I am, born and raised, yeah.

122
00:06:37,344 --> 00:06:39,624
A lot of the newsroom
is from here.

123
00:06:39,654 --> 00:06:41,174
Really feels like ah...

124
00:06:41,254 --> 00:06:43,174
like a local paper in that way.

125
00:06:43,473 --> 00:06:44,473
And did that changed at all

126
00:06:44,474 --> 00:06:46,414
after the paper were
sold to the Times?

127
00:06:48,054 --> 00:06:50,774
No. I don't think that big impact.

128
00:06:51,254 --> 00:06:52,374
Good.

129
00:06:54,284 --> 00:06:57,944
And... You're an editor
for the Spotlight team.

130
00:06:57,974 --> 00:06:59,574
I prefer to think of myself...

131
00:06:59,594 --> 00:07:01,194
as a player-coach, but yes.

132
00:07:01,624 --> 00:07:03,194
Are you familiar
with the Spotlight?

133
00:07:04,034 --> 00:07:05,174
No, not particularly.

134
00:07:05,214 --> 00:07:08,714
Well, we are a 4 person
investigative team.

135
00:07:09,004 --> 00:07:11,744
We report to Ben
Bradlee Jr. And...

136
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:13,904
we keep our work confidential.

137
00:07:15,614 --> 00:07:17,044
What are you working on now?

138
00:07:17,614 --> 00:07:19,044
We just put out a
piece on a shoddy...

139
00:07:19,154 --> 00:07:21,104
contraction outfit
and right now...

140
00:07:21,154 --> 00:07:24,444
we're really just trolling
around for our next story.

141
00:07:25,024 --> 00:07:27,084
How long does that typically take?

142
00:07:27,224 --> 00:07:29,584
Hard to say, a couple months.

143
00:07:30,724 --> 00:07:31,754
Couple months?

144
00:07:31,824 --> 00:07:33,754
Yeah, we don't like to rush it.

145
00:07:34,094 --> 00:07:36,044
Once we settle on the project...

146
00:07:36,114 --> 00:07:39,224
we can spend a year or
more investigating.

147
00:07:42,204 --> 00:07:44,794
- Is that a concern?
- Not necessarily.

148
00:07:45,404 --> 00:07:47,874
But, but from what I
understand readership is down,

149
00:07:47,904 --> 00:07:50,244
the Internet is cutting into
the Classified business.

150
00:07:50,264 --> 00:07:54,494
And, I think I'm gonna need to
take a hard look at things.

151
00:07:55,454 --> 00:07:59,064
So... You anticipate more cuts?

152
00:08:00,684 --> 00:08:03,404
I think it's safe to
assume so, but...

153
00:08:04,194 --> 00:08:06,064
what I'm more focused
on right now is...

154
00:08:06,144 --> 00:08:08,594
finding the way to
make this paper...

155
00:08:09,434 --> 00:08:11,114
essential to its readers.

156
00:08:12,304 --> 00:08:13,904
I like to think it already is.

157
00:08:15,474 --> 00:08:19,194
Fair enough. I just think
that we can do better.

158
00:08:31,524 --> 00:08:32,874
- Mr Bradlee.
- Hey.

159
00:08:33,154 --> 00:08:34,960
Saw the PD numbers,
looks interesting?

160
00:08:34,961 --> 00:08:36,414
Yeah, there's something there.

161
00:08:36,624 --> 00:08:38,844
- How long do you need?
- Another week.

162
00:08:39,824 --> 00:08:42,074
- Where are you going?
- 10:30.

163
00:08:42,394 --> 00:08:43,444
Since when?

164
00:08:43,764 --> 00:08:46,914
- Technically I am an editor.
- Technically.

165
00:08:47,604 --> 00:08:49,524
Your sit down with
Baron go that well?

166
00:08:49,604 --> 00:08:51,524
I couldn't get a read on him.

167
00:08:51,644 --> 00:08:52,814
That's a first.

168
00:08:52,864 --> 00:08:53,914
How about you?

169
00:08:53,944 --> 00:08:55,884
Oh, he's a barrel of laughs.

170
00:08:57,414 --> 00:08:59,214
Morning everyone.
Lets get started.

171
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:01,714
Do you want to say
something, Marty?

172
00:09:02,754 --> 00:09:03,814
Sure.

173
00:09:05,954 --> 00:09:06,954
Hello.

174
00:09:07,684 --> 00:09:09,974
As most of you know by now...

175
00:09:10,124 --> 00:09:11,574
my name is Marty Baron.

176
00:09:12,164 --> 00:09:14,994
I'm... delighted to be here.

177
00:09:17,464 --> 00:09:19,563
If you could tell me your
name as we go around...

178
00:09:19,564 --> 00:09:21,564
that'd be helpful. Thank you.

179
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:26,964
- Ok, Peter.
- Peter Canellos, Metro.

180
00:09:28,074 --> 00:09:30,394
We've got a major
Big Dig closure...

181
00:09:32,144 --> 00:09:34,014
- Hey, Steve.
- Mike.

182
00:09:34,114 --> 00:09:35,174
Hey.

183
00:09:35,554 --> 00:09:37,194
Crappy game last night.

184
00:09:37,554 --> 00:09:39,194
They can't hit worth a nickel.

185
00:09:39,224 --> 00:09:43,064
Listen, what's, what's Eileen
McNamara doing in 10:30?

186
00:09:43,794 --> 00:09:45,024
You need something, Mike?

187
00:09:45,163 --> 00:09:46,163
No. Just curious?

188
00:09:46,164 --> 00:09:48,564
Go be curious somewhere
else. I got work to do.

189
00:09:48,834 --> 00:09:51,034
- Ok Steve, see you.
- Yeah.

190
00:09:51,634 --> 00:09:54,044
And it looks like Pedro is going
to be out till September 1st.

191
00:09:54,504 --> 00:09:55,844
Jimmy says he could
be back this year,

192
00:09:55,884 --> 00:09:57,524
but the doctor
didn't seem so sure.

193
00:09:57,804 --> 00:09:59,304
When's the Pats opener?

194
00:10:03,044 --> 00:10:05,944
- Is that everyone?
- Yes, that's it.

195
00:10:06,444 --> 00:10:08,424
Ok, good, thank you.

196
00:10:09,554 --> 00:10:13,124
Did everyone read Eileen
McNamara column this weekend?

197
00:10:14,354 --> 00:10:17,664
- That's the Geoghan case?
- Yeah. What's the folo on that?

198
00:10:18,424 --> 00:10:21,794
It's a column, what kind of
follow would you thinking?

199
00:10:22,494 --> 00:10:25,644
Well, apparently this
priest molested kids...

200
00:10:25,664 --> 00:10:27,904
in 6 different parishes
over the last 30 years.

201
00:10:27,924 --> 00:10:29,191
And the attorney for
the victims, Mr

202
00:10:29,964 --> 00:10:31,084
Garabedian.

203
00:10:31,124 --> 00:10:34,254
Thanks Eileen. Mr Garabedian
says Cardinal Law...

204
00:10:34,284 --> 00:10:36,344
found about it 15 years
ago and did nothing.

205
00:10:36,374 --> 00:10:38,114
Yeah, I think that attorney
is a bit of crank...

206
00:10:38,144 --> 00:10:39,604
and the Church
dismissed the claim.

207
00:10:39,634 --> 00:10:40,954
He said, she said.

208
00:10:40,994 --> 00:10:43,314
Whether Mr Garabedian
is a crank or not...

209
00:10:43,334 --> 00:10:45,614
he says he has documents to
prove that Cardinal knew.

210
00:10:45,784 --> 00:10:48,004
And as I understand that those
documents are under a seal.

211
00:10:48,044 --> 00:10:50,674
Ok, but the fact remains
that Boston priest...

212
00:10:50,704 --> 00:10:52,934
abused 80 kids. We
have a lawyer...

213
00:10:52,964 --> 00:10:54,954
who says he can prove
Law knew about it...

214
00:10:54,984 --> 00:10:56,294
and we written all of...

215
00:10:56,314 --> 00:10:58,294
2 stories in the last 6 months.

216
00:10:59,204 --> 00:11:01,504
This strikes me as an
essential story...

217
00:11:01,524 --> 00:11:03,864
to a local paper, I think
that at very least...

218
00:11:03,874 --> 00:11:06,044
we have to go through
those documents.

219
00:11:06,574 --> 00:11:08,014
How would you like to do that?

220
00:11:09,044 --> 00:11:11,734
Well, I don't know what
the laws are here,

221
00:11:11,744 --> 00:11:13,934
but in Florida, we
would go to Court.

222
00:11:14,514 --> 00:11:16,144
You want to sue the Church?

223
00:11:16,944 --> 00:11:18,704
Technically we wouldn't
sue the Church...

224
00:11:18,724 --> 00:11:21,504
we'd file a motion to lift
the seal on those documents.

225
00:11:21,624 --> 00:11:23,564
The Church would read
that as us suing them.

226
00:11:24,224 --> 00:11:25,364
So will everybody else.

227
00:11:26,864 --> 00:11:27,884
Good to know.

228
00:11:31,294 --> 00:11:32,954
Gutsy call for a first day.

229
00:11:32,984 --> 00:11:33,994
That's one word for it.

230
00:11:34,124 --> 00:11:35,934
How do you think that's
gonna play down front?

231
00:11:35,954 --> 00:11:37,804
I think Gilman's
gonna shit a brick.

232
00:11:38,074 --> 00:11:39,494
- Hey.
- Door.

233
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:41,074
How did it go?

234
00:11:41,544 --> 00:11:43,444
Well, Baron wants to sue for...

235
00:11:43,474 --> 00:11:45,344
the sealed docs in
the Geoghan case.

236
00:11:45,584 --> 00:11:48,194
