00:12:10,504 --> 00:12:11,924
Baron wants to talk to us.

245
00:12:12,644 --> 00:12:13,644
Us?

246
00:12:14,244 --> 00:12:18,214
Ok Jim, thank you.
Yes. Ok, thanks.

247
00:12:20,414 --> 00:12:23,694
I've set up a meeting for
tomorrow with outside counsellor.

248
00:12:23,854 --> 00:12:25,364
- Jon Albano.
- Yeah.

249
00:12:25,624 --> 00:12:26,924
Who's the Judge in this case?

250
00:12:29,754 --> 00:12:32,194
- Constance Sweeney.
- Tough.

251
00:12:32,764 --> 00:12:35,024
- Why is that?
- Good catholic girl.

252
00:12:37,694 --> 00:12:38,694
So...

253
00:12:39,124 --> 00:12:41,054
Judging from what I've
read, it doesn't seem...

254
00:12:41,084 --> 00:12:44,014
like we've done the very thorough
investigation in the Geoghan case?

255
00:12:44,384 --> 00:12:45,414
Is that right?

256
00:12:45,544 --> 00:12:47,014
No. It's not.

257
00:12:47,444 --> 00:12:48,594
